'''David Despin''' is a [[French people|French]] [[rugby league]] player and coach who represented [[France national rugby league team|his country]] in the [[1995 Rugby League World Cup|1995]] and [[2000 Rugby League World Cup|2000 World Cups]].
==Playing career==
Despin played for the [[Villeneuve Leopards]] in French domestic tournaments. He first represented [[France national rugby league team|France]] in 1991. He remained part of the French squad for the rest of the decade, being selected in the [[1995 Rugby League World Cup|1995]] and [[2000 Rugby League World Cup|2000 World Cup]] teams.<ref>[http://www.independent.co.uk/sport/rugby-league-schofield-sounds-note-of-caution-great-britains-captain-pleased-by-the-return-of-crooks-1430227.html Schofield sounds note of caution: Great Britain's captain pleased by the return of Crooks] ''The Independent'', 19 March 1994</ref> In 1997 Despin was part of Frances [[rugby league nines|nines]] squad that competed in the [[Rugby League World Nines]] tournament.<ref>[http://www.rugby-league-world.com/1997/Results/RepMatches/nines.html World Nines Tournament] ''rugby-league-world.com''</ref>

In 1996 he joined the new [[Paris Saint-Germain Rugby League|Paris Saint-Germain]] side in [[Super League I]]. After the season ended he returned to the Leopards and was part of their 2000 and 2001 [[Challenge Cup]] runs.<ref>[http://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/rugbyleague/3000277/Three-banned-after-brawl.html Three banned after brawl] ''The Telegraph'', 6 March 2001</ref> 

Despin later coached Villeneuve.
